name: Satu Titik Kopi Barito
address: Jl. Tukad Barito No.36x, Dauh Puri Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80225, Indonesia
review 1:
Wow this place is a hidden gem. Love the setting and the open concept. Prices are cheap and the staff are very friendly and helpful. Coffee is up there with the best. Their kitchen is small and hence cannot handle many orders of food quickly.

Lastly I would say i feel the oldest here as there are mostly young adults hereüòÅ
review 2: The food is delicious, the service is friendly, but the place is super crowded with average live music. Not too good for meeting, just hangout
review 3: Good place to spend time with friend and also u can find your future wife or gf here
review 4: good place to spend time with friends, but sometime feels uncomfortable when the customer are overload.
review 5: Perfect coffee, good service, good music and fast wi-fi makes this place a wonderful location.

name: Calla Resto & Coffee
address: Jl. Tukad Batanghari No.40, Panjer, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80225, Indonesia
review 1:
Positives are the staff was friendly and helpful and spacious parking space. The food was okay but not really justifying the price.

Highlight of this place was the place itself. It reminds me of myself building a place in The Sims game with money cheat. Huge renaissance style paintings, huge statues, high ceilings. I used to throw all of the expensive decorations in the place and this place is like the real life of my The Sims houses back then. The music also loud.

I‚Äôm sure this place built with all the best intentions, it just doesn‚Äôt doing it for me.

Another note was the restroom which sadly was not built extravagantly like my The Sims builds. It can be a little bit more cleaner, brighter and better air circulations those will help the place tremendously.

I‚Äôd still recommend people to visit tho, just for them to experience my The Sims-like decorations in real life.
review 2:
We decided to look for a new place to try and I found this place on google map.

The venue was huge and spacious. With kitsch and over the top decor which sort of eye catchy and made the place looked "different".

Food was good, with wide range options from Indonesian to Western. The portions were generous and the price were very reasonable.

The staff were very friendly and attentive.
review 3: Surprisingly good! I ordered a beef hotplate and the beef was tender, chewy and delicious. The serving is also quite huge. Inside was quite large and there was a billiard table and children's playground. Parking is quite large for cars and scooters.
review 4:
The staff are friendly and service was great.
Food is good.
Price is not too expensive.
review 5:
this place is really good and big enough for birthday party, they have backyard before and was so beautiful outdoor but now the make it indoor, also the have like room on the left side i think it can be meeting room.
last time i ordered brownies and pain au chocolat but that was too dry like not fresh
they have the stage for live music also
they have 8pool there!

japanese ice coffee tastes good but doesn't like the presentation. Thank u for free cold water üôèüèª

Coffee is really good, service is also good. Staffs are friendly. Wifi is pretty strong if you need to do work here, there‚Äôs no AC but still quite cooling on a hot afternoon.

Very interesting set up and decoration. They seems to have a lot of certifications and also take pride in their coffee making. Their gesha filter coffee sold out, maybe can come earlier. We tried their v60 and ice signature karakter.

name: Goory Coffee & Eatery
address: Jl. Tukad Barito Timur No.5, Panjer, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80225, Indonesia
review 1:
Having some snack in this fancy looks cafe, very nice place, comfy (but recomend for doing some work on laptop, the table was to high) and obviusly clean..
We were ordering meat lover pizza and tacos, size of the pizza was quite big, but the ginger taste on the sauce was too strong, tacos was little bit bland, tortilla was cold but the prices was affordable, considering the location in the heart of Denpasar. Highly recomend to try the strawberry iced tea. Service was good, all staff were very friendly. They even asked about ‚Äúhow was the food‚Äù when we pay the bill, something we didn‚Äôt get in any other cafes around. If we can give a suggestion, please ask that question after the first or second bite, so you guys how‚Äôs the food‚Ä¶
review 2:
I will review this cafe by 3 indicators :

1. The foods
I and my friends ordered several menus such as beef burger, carbonara spaghetti, chicken parmigiana, hamburg fries, and some beverages. Overall the foods had good taste, the price was also affordable for this kind of cafe. But personally I didnt like the beef burger‚Äôs patty because it was quite dry. I highly recommend you to try their carbonara spaghetti!üëç

2. The service
All staffs had great manner and really polite. They tried to give us the best service, I love it!

3. The ambience
This cafe‚Äôs ambience was suitable for you who are looking for a place to have a dinner with your friends, and take some instagramable photos. Yeah, they had several aesthetic spots so you can pose and take some photos there.

Went there when they are still soft opening, have a nice dinner there, cozy place to hang out with friends or working alone there. They offer so many sofa to seat and electricity socket  to work there. Also they have small kids playground right there.

Nice and friendly staff also. They recommend their Special Dishes which is Goory Noodles..
review 4: Trying to have new experiences by choosing random cafe in random areas and found Goory on the way. Nice cozy cafe, good food, good vibes, and friendly staff. Well done Goory and Thank you üåπüôè
review 5: The food was delicious, the place was great,  the mini playground was beautiful, safe and clean. But the live music was too loud outdoor, we can‚Äôt talk to our friends normally but that‚Äôs okay the singers was so talented ü´∂üèª One thing you guys should make some kids menu cause there is a mini playground and of course we bring our children ü•∞ will comeback again soon ‚ù£Ô∏è

I will come again with my family when the holidays arrive üòäüëçüèª

Can eat like a glutton for under Rp. 150,000 per person

name: Kataramen Bali
address: Jl. Tukad Barito No.16, Panjer, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80225, Indonesia
review 1: The ramen tastes amazing! The broth is so rich in flavors! I ordered the signature kataramen and the naruto maki ramen, both tasted fresh and flavorful. The chocolate custard pudding is tasty too. They might want to fix the indoor AC though, because it gets really hot indoors, we barely feel the AC. The staff is super nice too to make sure we ordered the right menu to get the ongoing promotion. Definitely coming back here sometimes.
review 2: The signature beef ramen was super salty üëé. The karaage was actually good. All the waiting staff looked so tired they couldn't smile at anyone, totally different than the kitchen staff who joked and laughed.
review 3: If you're looking for a budget friendly option, this place is a winner! The ramen is nothing extraordinary, but the prices are hard to beat. What's impressive is the excellent service and the cozy Japanese atmosphere, complete with anime music. Perfect for a quick and affordable meal!
review 4: Not a huge fan of their ramen but the atmosphere really comfy. Please have a look on the AC and it‚Äôs a bit hot when it‚Äôs already 16 degrees.
review 5: I had a delightful experience at Kataramen Bali. The signature beef kataramen was delicious, though the sauce was a tad salty for my taste. The service and atmosphere both earned solid 5 stars. It's worth noting that there's no pork on the menu, which could be a plus or a consideration for some. Overall, a positive dining experience.

address: Jl. Tukad Badung VIII No.16, Renon, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80226, Indonesia
review 1: One of my favorite coffee shop in Bali (well, Denpasar area).. Homey and comfy, great service. Trying their manual brew (Huta Batak beans) and it was so good.

review 4: So sad pesan caesar salad 30k isinya hanya lettuce dan chicken ham in a tiny bowl.. but i love the ambience though. But really not worthed for the food

name: Laoban Kopitiam Denpasar
address: Jl. Tukad Barito Timur No.35, Panjer, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80225, Indonesia
review 1:

review 3: The dim sum and teh tarik were good. The rice menu was just okay. There were a lot of tables, but the indoor area was too narrow. However, the staff were friendly and helpful.
review 4: Best place for breakfast or any kind of meals, very comforting and delicious. place was good and staff were friendly.
review 5:
As per 8th feb 2024, They opened but not fully prepared. As usual people flock to brand new place in denpasar so expect difficulties of getting a seat. Car park also difficult, better ride motorbike.

What we order :

Mie Ayam, not that good.  But it's according to my friend so I can't explain..

Nasi mala, breaded chicken a bit too dry and salty for my taste.
Portion is small. But enough for female.

Siomay is 3 pcs small size siomay. Decent taste but considering the price... not in a good balance.

Kulit tahu. Surprisingly decent filling. But kinda oily.  Should be strained more, but it came super late so can't be helped.

Kaya toast, unlike the picture on the menu, it's thin toasted bread, barely taste the kaya jam. I got better kaya toast at Chinese warung at dalung area  for less the price . So this kaya toast is a letdown.

Staff seems to be overwhelmed and lack of direction. Our dumplings came super late. It supposed to be appettizer, not dessert.
Management, pls do better.

I'd say the level of food in this place similar to mie gacoan but a bit more expensive and have Singapore peranakan food gimmick.

address: Jl. Tukad Batanghari No.69, Dauh Puri Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80225, Indonesia

review 4: One kids attraction to try when you come to Mall Level 21. The entrance fee is 50k for 1,5 hours. They will charge the carer for 10k and give you a pair of shock to be allowed to enter. The area is not that big but the layout is good enough to give another level of playing. You will be called if the time is up
review 5:
Gurita Playground is a great place for kids to go play, and find new friends they can play alongside with. They have a section outside and one inside were you can order foodstuffs and drinks. Although the selection is not very large, it is certainly good enough for the waiting parents.
Staff is very kind and courteous. The place is very clean and now in these pandemic times, they disinfect every day each and every ball for example in the ballpit area, which is impressive.
I have only good things to say about Gurita Playground, and we will certainly go there again.
One downside is that there are timelimits on the visits, meaning you pay for a certain period of time whereas other similar places usually pay once and the child(ren) can play until they are finished and tired.
Other than that, we had very positive experience at Gurita Playground and i have no issues in recommending this playground for your child, children. My daughter thoroughly enjoyed her time there, and we have visited several times.

Is your child bored or need to meet other kids Gurita Playground provide that and take care of your needs while waiting as your child plays.

Highly recommended. Gurita Playground is top of the line Playground, and you should try the place out.

Only good things to say to Gurita Playground. Thumbs up üëçüëç‚úÖ
